      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW ULA (2) was a winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time and could manage only a 3.5 lengths 7th at Shepparton (23.28). Has ability and is a key runner. RITA SKEETER (8) produced a modest effort most recently when eighth at this track over 390m behind Centrefold Sal (23.09) in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Has the ability to give this a shake. ELSA ESCARGOT (4) looks close to win after hitting the frame last run (22.85) at this track in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win. Has first look at box 4 this time. The form out of her last race has been franked. Will give a great sight again. CAN SHE YAP (7) can sneak into the finish while fresh.",
